<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 10:26PM CST  by NWS Lake Charles</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT TYLER...NEWTON...EASTERN HARDIN
AND JASPER COUNTIES THROUGH 1115 PM CST...
At 1021 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking areas of showers and
intermittent thundesrstorms across Southeast Texas, producing
periods of pea to penny sized hail.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lumberton, Jasper, Silsbee, Woodville, Newton, Kirbyville, Kountze,
Deweyville, Evadale, Warren, Town Bluff, Toledo Bend Dam, Call,
Ebenezer, Fred, Wildwood, Bon Weir, Buna, Burkeville, and Bevil Oaks.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
